ğŸš€ Quick Start
Prerequisites
Bashnode >= 18.0.0
npm >= 9.0.0
git
1. Clone the Repository
Bashgit clone https://github.com/mja2001/VaultLink.git
cd VaultLink
2. Install Dependencies
Bash# Install frontend dependencies
npm install
# Install smart contract dependencies
cd contracts
npm install
cd ..
3. Environment Setup
Create a .env.local file in the root directory:
env# Ethereum RPC URLs
NEXT_PUBLIC_ALCHEMY_KEY=your_alchemy_api_key
NEXT_PUBLIC_INFURA_KEY=your_infura_api_key
# MNEE Contract Address
NEXT_PUBLIC_MNEE_CONTRACT=0x8ccedbAe4916b79da7F3F612EfB2EB93A2bFD6cF
# Contract Addresses (after deployment)
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTENT_VAULT_ADDRESS=your_deployed_contract_address
NEXT_PUBLIC_REVENUE_STREAMER_ADDRESS=your_deployed_contract_address
NEXT_PUBLIC_SPLIT_PAYMENT_ADDRESS=your_deployed_contract_address
# IPFS Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_IPFS_GATEWAY=https://ipfs.io/ipfs/
PINATA_API_KEY=your_pinata_api_key
PINATA_SECRET_KEY=your_pinata_secret_key
# WalletConnect Project ID
NEXT_PUBLIC_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id
4. Compile Smart Contracts
Bashcd contracts
npx hardhat compile
5. Deploy Contracts (Testnet)
Bash# Deploy to Sepolia testnet
npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.js --network sepolia
# Copy deployed addresses to .env.local
6. Run Development Server
Bashcd ..
npm run dev
Open http://localhost:3000 in your browser.

